# gen36: the generative inference loop (DESIGN D-prop1). parrot0 generates
# autoregressively -- emit a word, append it to the working context, re-infer
# the next word, repeat -- but driven by repeated deterministic inference, not a
# neural pass. The continuation relation cont(prev, word) is INDUCED from
# examples ("learn sequence:"), never hand-authored, so this is a tiny learned
# language model, not a phrasebook. gen36 picks the first continuation by
# insertion order; frequency weighting comes in gen37. Held-out tokens.
> learn sequence: alpha beta gamma delta
< Learned 3 transition(s).
# Decode from a seed: follow the learned transitions until none remain.
> say alpha
< alpha beta gamma delta
> say gamma
< gamma delta
# A seed with no learned continuation generates just itself -- no invention.
> say lonely
< lonely
# The loop conditions on its own output: a cycle in the data streams until the
# step bound, rather than looping forever.
> learn sequence: ping pong ping
< Learned 2 transition(s).
> say ping
< ping pong ping pong ping pong ping pong ping pong ping pong ping pong ping pong ping pong ping pong ping pong ping pong ping